4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would require high schools to allow
6 high school students participating in organized
7 National Signing Day activities related to the
8 acceptance of athletic scholarships, postsecondary
9 school educational commitments, apprenticeship
10 programs, and military enlistments to be excused from
11 class.
12 This bill would also require high schools to
13 provide reasonable accommodations for those activities.
14
15
16 A BILL
17 TO BE ENTITLED
18 AN ACT
19
20 Relating to public high schools; to require high
21 schools to excuse students from class to participate in
22 National Signing Day activities related to the acceptance of
23 athletic scholarships, postsecondary school educational
24 commitments, apprenticeship programs, and military
25 enlistments; and to provide reasonable accommodations for
26 those activities.
27 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
28 Section 1. (a) High school students participating
Page 1

Section 1. (a) High school students participating
HB75 INTRODUCED
29 during instructional time at school in organized National
30 Signing Day activities related to the acceptance of athletic
31 scholarships, postsecondary school educational commitments,
32 commitments to apprenticeship programs, and military
33 enlistments shall be excused from class.
34 (b) Reasonable accommodations shall be provided for
35 activities conducted pursuant to subsection (a). For purposes
36 of this section, reasonable accommodations shall include, but
37 not be limited to, meeting space with connectivity access and
38 seating.
39 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
40 1, 2026.
